  "body": "Having a simple function definition that receives 2 booleans get an infinite estimated gas:\r\n\r\n``` solidity \r\ncontract Checker{\r\n    function check(bool visited, bool isOk)public {}\r\n}\r\n``` \r\n\r\nI have been playing and looks like doesn't happen only with Booleans but also for other types when receiving more than one parameter with the same type.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"603\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-30 at 20 47 28\" src=\"https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/assets/26546018/a27c10f4-8826-47b4-9249-7cbf5b19a571\">\r\n\r\n\r\nBut it calculates it correctly if each param has a different type\r\n\r\n<img width=\"599\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-30 at 20 44 03\" src=\"https://github.com/ethereum/remix-project/assets/26546018/089a469d-52f7-4da2-8ef4-6fc215e6ab81\">\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what could be happening but, I would expect a possible gas estimation in all cases.\r\n",
